{
  "texts": [
    "Three different Gaussian likelihoods are used to give parameter posterior distribution: L0: Without applying the delensing process, just use the observed power spectrum C l directly with theoretical model given in Eq.(2.39).",
    "L1:The power spectrum C l described by the theoretical model given in Eq.(2.39).",
    "L2:The power spectrum C l described by the theoretical model given in Eq.",
    "(2.40).L3: Instead of applying the delensing process to the lensed maps, treat the lensing template as an additional pseudo-channel and calculate the auto and cross power spectra to create the theoretical model vector.",
    "Details can be found in Appendix C.The Gaussian log-likelihood used in this work is given by:-2 ln L(C ℓ | Ĉℓ) = (X ℓ -Xℓ) T M -1 ℓ (X ℓ -Xℓ) + ln |M ℓ | (4.10)where the vector Xℓ contains the band-power estimates from the observed cut-sky maps, calculated using the NaMaster code."
  ]
}